<item>
            <title>[JCRVLT-100] FileVault requires access to root node</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/JCRVLT-100</link>
                <project id="12314920" key="JCRVLT">Jackrabbit FileVault</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Based on the JCRLT-99 i searched the code base for additional places where access to the root node is required.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=tripod&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;tripod&quot;&gt;tripod&lt;/a&gt;, in the attached &lt;tt&gt;filevault_root_access.txt&lt;/tt&gt; you can find the complete result for searching the jcrvlt code base for &lt;tt&gt;getRootNode&lt;/tt&gt;. some seemed to be valid shortcuts (marked with &lt;em&gt;(excluded)&lt;/em&gt;) but i suspect that others might require some attention.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;if using the functionality provided with a non-admin session, access to the root node is likely to not be granted thus rendering the filevault unusable (or risking privilege escalations by being forced to grant a non-privileged session full access up to the root node).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;i will create individual subtasks for the various parts that IMHO need to be fixed.&lt;/p&gt;
</description>
